A Chief Magistrate Court in Agbara, Ogun State, has remanded one Adekunle Ajose on charges of land grabbing and murder. Ajose, popularly known as Baba Isila, was arraigned yesterday charged with terrorising landowners in Ikogbo and Imose communities in the Ado-Odo/Ota council of the state. The defendant and others said to be on the run, are facing a seven-count charge, including conspiracy to commit murder, murder and willful destruction of property on or before September 23, 2021.   Let ‘dear Sylvester Oromoni’s soul rest,’ Dowen College…     Man loses three children to midnight fire     ‘Govt never told states to enforce compulsory vaccination of…   They were alleged to have killed one Matthew Opaleye and destroyed building blocks and moulding machine equipment, among other allegations. The court ordered that the accused be remanded in a custodial centre pending the Attorney-General’s advice. - Advertisement - The case was adjourned till March 17, 2022.